"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-08-01-Paris-first-women-s-dragon-boat-team-appears-at-2024-Summer-Olympics-1vI9CNYP184-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  CGTN  Copied  Dragon boat racing has been featured as a demonstration sport at the 2024 Olympics. And Paris' first women's team of this exciting water sport, mainly composed of breast cancer survivors, participated in the torch relay. Since it was established in 2016, the team has been practicing on a weekly basis for the past eight years. Team leader Carole designed a logo with intertwined dragons and phoenixes, reflecting their journey of overcoming pain and rising anew. The team said it is proud to represent Chinese culture in Paris, especially during this milestone year for France-China relations.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"